&lt;div class="sect2"&gt;
&lt;h3 id="_ohs_nos_im_hitting_a_java_lang_exception_no_datastore_implementation_specified"&gt;Ohs Nos! I&amp;#8217;m hitting a java.lang.Exception: No datastore implementation specified&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="paragraph"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error means that you probably haven&amp;#8217;t specified your datastore type in your application.groovy or application.yml file.
This plugin has an auto-index feature which automatically propagates any changes made to searchable Domains into the search index;
this is done by hooking into GORM&amp;#8217;s storage events but also requires a reference to the active datastore implementation.
To fix, edit your project&amp;#8217;s application.groovy or application.yml file and add:
application.groovy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="listingblock"&gt;
&lt;div class="content"&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;elasticSearch {
    ...
    datastoreImpl = 'nameOfDatastoreBean'
    ...
}&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="paragraph"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;application.yml&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="listingblock"&gt;
&lt;div class="content"&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;elasticSearch:
    datastoreImpl: nameOfDatastoreBean&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="paragraph"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Where the value should be the name of the datastore bean as it is configured in the Spring context; some possible values:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="dlist"&gt;
&lt;dl&gt;
&lt;dt class="hdlist1"&gt;MongoDB&lt;/dt&gt;
&lt;dd&gt;
&lt;p&gt;mongoDatastore&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/dd&gt;
&lt;dt class="hdlist1"&gt;Hibernate&lt;/dt&gt;
&lt;dd&gt;
&lt;p&gt;hibernateDatastore&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/dd&gt;
&lt;/dl&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
